data.value:
This ArcGIS Add-In tool computes geographical accessibility scores using Floating Catchment Area and other methods. It requires a map layer of points to represent the locations of service supply, and another to represent the locations of service demand. An ESRI Network Layer is also needed to compute travel time/distance between these two inputs. The points in both layers must be "pre-snapped" onto the network layer (see the "Calculate Locations" tool in Network Analyst Toolbox).
FCA scores and other computed accessibility metrics are output to an ArcGIS table. The FCA scores are based either on the 'classic' or the 'enhanced' algorithms. For further instruction, see accompanying documentation.
Click the right-arrow to begin...
